362,IssuesEvent,2018-07-16 05:45:19+00:00,32288304,aleaxit/gmpy,1645935,casevh,,,closed,Spurious overflow error in bincoef,[],[],1,"I am investigating a test failure in sympy, from an invocation of bincoef.  With 2.0.8:

```
>>> gmpy2.bincoef(mpz(79232165267303928292058750056084441948572511312165380965440075720159859792344339983120618959044048198214221915637090855535036339620413440000),6)
mpz()
```

With 2.1.0a2:

```
gmpy2.bincoef(mpz(79232165267303928292058750056084441948572511312165380965440075720159859792344339983120618959044048198214221915637090855535036339620413440000),6)
OverflowError: value too large to convert to C unsigned long

The above exception was the direct cause of the following exception:

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""<stdin>"", line 1, in <module>
SystemError: <built-in function bincoef> returned a result with an error set
```

A call to PyErr_Clear() should be inserted at line 798 of gmpy2_mpz_misc.c.  I tested, and this does indeed fix the problem.",{},{}
