410,IssuesEvent,2016-11-12 11:38:04+00:00,44054354,dabeaz/curio,1560652,aktiur,,,closed,spawn hanging in master when using list comprehensions (?!),[],[],7,"Hello all,

I was playing with Curio using the master branch version and trying to write a small chat server to understand the concepts when I came across what looks like a weird bug.

### Curio and Python version
master (0e2a274d27784fa641f3aa3adda9a4a75b8b1436)

```
>>> print(sys.version)
3.5.2 (default, Sep 10 2016, 08:21:44) 
[GCC 5.4.0 20160609]
```
### Code used
The full code I used is there https://gist.github.com/aktiur/169fa7a3c86501f6ec380c353c6642bd
But here is the relevant part:
```python
async def spawn_and_wait_all(coros):
    tasks = []
    for coro in coros:
        task = await curio.spawn(coro)
        tasks.append(task)
    for task in tasks:
        await task.join()

async def sendall(content):
    coros = [queue.put(content) for queue in queues]
    await spawn_and_wait_all(coros)
```

### Bug summary
When `sendall` is awaited, if `queues` is not empty, the task will hang with 100 % cpu load. The monitor reports the following information:

```
curio > ps
Task   State        Cycles     Timeout Task                                               
------ ------------ ---------- ------- --------------------------------------------------
0      READ_WAIT    1          None    Kernel.run.<locals>._kernel_task                  
1      FUTURE_WAIT  2          None    Monitor.monitor_task                              
4      RUNNING      5          None    _run_server.<locals>.run_client                   
5      QUEUE_GET    3          None    _client_writer                                    
7      RUNNING      735641     None    Kernel.run.<locals>._shutdown_tasks               
curio > where 4
Stack for Task(id=4, <coroutine object _run_server.<locals>.run_client at 0x7fd9b8727678>, state='RUNNING') (most recent call last):
  File ""/home/arthur/.envs/curio-essays/lib/python3.5/site-packages/curio/network.py"", line 82, in run_client
    await client_connected_task(client, addr)
  File ""chat_server.py"", line 32, in client_reader
    await sendall(name + b"": "" + line)
  File ""chat_server.py"", line 18, in sendall
    await spawn_and_wait_all(coros)
  File ""chat_server.py"", line 11, in spawn_and_wait_all
    task = await curio.spawn(coro)
  File ""/home/arthur/.envs/curio-essays/lib/python3.5/site-packages/curio/task.py"", line 137, in spawn
    return await _spawn(coro, daemon)
  File ""/home/arthur/.envs/curio-essays/lib/python3.5/site-packages/curio/traps.py"", line 85, in _spawn
    return (yield _trap_spawn, coro, daemon)

curio > where 7
Stack for Task(id=7, <coroutine object Kernel.run.<locals>._shutdown_tasks at 0x7fd9b8727b48>, state='RUNNING') (most recent call last):
  File ""/home/arthur/.envs/curio-essays/lib/python3.5/site-packages/curio/kernel.py"", line 320, in _shutdown_tasks
    await task.cancel()
  File ""/home/arthur/.envs/curio-essays/lib/python3.5/site-packages/curio/task.py"", line 81, in cancel
    result = await self.cancel_no_wait()
  File ""/home/arthur/.envs/curio-essays/lib/python3.5/site-packages/curio/task.py"", line 95, in cancel_no_wait
