2025,IssuesEvent,2017-03-03 19:24:53+00:00,20101515,giampaolo/psutil,79831,maxbelanger,,,opened,Crash in `Process.open_files` when it times out,[],[],0,"We've observed that psutil can crash in a call to `DeleteFiber` when trying to clean up the `NtQueryObject` thread if it takes too long. This is reproducing primarily on recent versions of Windows (8.1, 10) when building using the Windows 8.1 SDK and manually inducing the call to `psutil_NtQueryObject` to time out by adding a breakpoint on `NtQueryObject`.",{},{}
2031,IssuesEvent,2017-03-04 09:29:54+00:00,20101515,giampaolo/psutil,681260,giampaolo,,,closed,Windows - psutil.test() cpu_percent = 0,[],[],1,"Hi,

