2601,IssuesEvent,2017-09-06 16:20:28+00:00,23058769,nabla-c0d3/sslyze,1915165,nabla-c0d3,,,closed,nassl requirement issue with latest (1.1.3) SSLyze release,[],[],1,"Currently, the tag for the `1.1.3` `SSLyze` release has 2 irreconcilable version dependencies on `nassl`. `setup.py` contains the requirement ['nassl>=0.16.0,<0.17.0'](https://github.com/nabla-c0d3/sslyze/blob/1.1.3/setup.py#L17) while `requirements.txt` has the requirement ['nassl>=0.17.0,<0.18.0'](https://github.com/nabla-c0d3/sslyze/blob/1.1.3/requirements.txt#L1).

If I blindly patch `setup.py` to support the newer version of `nassl` it _seems_ to work, but I think it is best to report the issue here.",{},{}
