2795,IssuesEvent,2016-06-23 19:18:28+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,8171029,Boduje,,,opened,Sticky header not calculating position correctly,[],[],0,"I've been using Tablesorter now for some time and love it!  I recently updated a website layout and now my tablesorter tables are no longer in DIVs.  They are centered using CSS (margin:0 auto;) with a maximum width.

The problem I am experiencing come from differences in how browsers calculate the position of the sticky header.

Here is the code in Firefox 46:
`<div style=""position: fixed; top: 0px; left: 328px; visibility: visible; z-index: 2; width: 1248px;"" class=""tablesorter-sticky-wrapper tablesorter-sticky-visible"">`

Here is the code in Chrome 51:
`<div style=""position: fixed; top: 0px; left: 0px; visibility: visible; z-index: 2; width: 1248px;"" class=""tablesorter-sticky-wrapper tablesorter-sticky-visible"" >`

You can see that Firefox has calculated the left positioning (328px) to keep the sticky header centered.  Google Chrome has not - left position is zero '0'.

Is this a bug or do I need to add something to the tablesorter init?",{},{}
