3785,IssuesEvent,2017-10-29 11:01:30+00:00,3727523,cyberdelia/metrology,5390500,cbouilla,,,opened,Meter.one_minute_rate is wrong and/or badly documented,[],[],0,"The following code:
```rate = Meter()
for i in range(int(65/0.05)):
     rate.mark()
     time.sleep(0.05)
print(rate.one_minute_rate)
print(rate.mean_rate)```

yields:
```12.744700289590714
19.916839105797937```

Why does the one-minute moving average differs from the average over the first minute?
",{},{}
