4739,IssuesEvent,2018-03-26 09:04:37+00:00,68616078,and3rson/flake8-colors,526577,Peque,,,opened,Default format,[],[],0,"It would be great if there was a default formatting, to avoid having to write the long, not-very-readable line in the configuration file:

```
format = ${cyan}%(path)s${reset}:${yellow_bold}%(row)d${reset}:${green_bold}%(col)d${reset}: ${red_bold}%(code)s${reset} %(text)
```

I do not care that much about the specific colors/bold. I guess it is reasonable to assume most people would be happy with any default colors (like the ones you chose).

- Maybe something like `format = colored`.
- Or it could be automatic by simply having `flake8-colors` installed.
- Or maybe have an option to run `flake8 --color` that automatically uses that line?",{},{}
