4848,IssuesEvent,2018-06-07 06:58:40+00:00,97002861,ljvmiranda921/pyswarms,12949683,ljvmiranda921,,,opened,Update documentation in Development Branch,"[{'id': 654552192, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw2NTQ1NTIxOTI=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ljvmiranda921/pyswarms/labels/documentation', 'name': 'documentation', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}, {'id': 645411972, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw2NDU0MTE5NzI=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ljvmiranda921/pyswarms/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '128A0C', 'default': True}]",[],0,"## Description

A lot of things have happened when we added the backend module in PR #115 . The API is still the same, but we changed the backend. It would be nice if we can add some documentation in ReadTheDocs for this backend. 

In addition, it would also be nice to add new notebook examples on how to use this backend to develop your own swarm algorithms without using the pre-made `GlobalBestPSO`, etc. implementations.

If you're up to the task, just ping me here! We'll be working together.

### Things to do:
- [ ] Add backend module (`.rst` files) in the ReadTheDocs documentation
- [ ] Maybe add a separate RTD docs for `master` and `development` branch?
- [ ] Use IPython shells as suggested in #107 
- [ ] Double-check any problems in Feature Selection as reported in #110 (do we need to incorporate a minimum number of 1s? Or is it too specific in feature selection already?)
- [ ] Jupyter notebook example on `backend` module (and clean-up/updates of existing notebooks if necessary).",{},{}
