5444,IssuesEvent,2017-05-01 16:14:14+00:00,695611,etianen/django-reversion,8999232,NogerbekNurzhan,,,closed,How to know version id which was reverted?,[],[],2,"Hello! I am little bit comfused. I want to know ID of version which was reverted. How to add this id in comment? Here you can see my view function.

**views.py:**
```
@reversion.create_revision()
def project_revert(request, project_code, project_reversion_id):
    project = get_object_or_404(Project, pk=project_code)

    revision = get_object_or_404(Version.objects.get_for_object(project), pk=project_reversion_id).revision
    revision_id = revision.id

    reversion.set_user(request.user)
    reversion.set_comment(""REVERT {}"".format(revision_id))

    revision.revert()
    return redirect('project:project_detail', project_code=project.code)
```

**urls.py:**
```
url(r'^(?P<project_code>[0-9a-f-]+)/(?P<project_reversion_id>\d+)/project_revert/$',
        project_revert,
        name='project_revert'),
```

**button in template:**
```
<a href=""{% url 'project:project_revert' project_code=project.code project_reversion_id=version.revision.id %}"">
      {% trans 'Revert' %}
</a>
```",{},{}
