6332,IssuesEvent,2018-01-16 18:36:20+00:00,32076778,elapouya/python-docx-template,5049984,jmanjohns2,,,opened,Odd Error on Output when ampersand (&) placed in footer,[],[],0,"Hey Guys,

I have a program that is working just fine 99.9% of the time and creates documents from a single word template. It works flawlessly *but* when and only when I try to place a string in the footer that contains an ampersand, the resulting output is corrupt and word won't open it. Libreoffice is less picky and opens the resulting doc, but the footer is empty only for those docs that won't open in word. I noticed this seemed to be happening only when the text I was trying to place included an Ampersand. I hacked my code to find and replace ampersands with a space and, voila, no more problems. Can you think of why this might be happening?

The error is not in python, it's in word, so I've attached an image of the exact error message and window. Definitely related to how the library is inserting the footer IMHO. 
![python docx template error](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5049984/35005614-ff33c458-fac1-11e7-86c0-6341510b5086.png)

Happy to place my code in here, but I'm not sure how helpful it will be. ",{},{}
