6391,IssuesEvent,2015-06-03 11:34:49+00:00,1576129,KristianOellegaard/django-hvad,4925587,barseghyanartur,,,opened,`filter_horizontal` in the TranslatableAdmin,[],[],0,I have a model with a ManyToMany field. In the admin (`TranslatableAdmin`) `filter_horizontal` does nothing. I see that `get_form` method of the `TranslatableAdmin` is tweaked. Any clear suggestions of how to enable the `filter_horizontal` are welcome.,{},{}
6422,IssuesEvent,2018-07-11 09:54:16+00:00,4025652,invisibleroads/socketIO-client,259463,yujiang,,,opened,About connect to the latest node.js socket.io server,[],[],0,"if you want to connect to a node.js socket.io server, you should modify the parsers.py as:

def _read_packet_length(content, content_index):
    end = content_index
    while content[end] != "":"":
        end += 1
    packet_length_string = content[content_index:end]
    end += 1    
    content_index = end
    #print(""_read_packet_length"",packet_length_string)
    return content_index, int(packet_length_string)


def _read_packet_text(content, content_index, packet_length):
    packet_text = content[content_index:content_index + packet_length]
    #print(""_read_packet_text"",packet_text)
    return content_index + packet_length, packet_text
",{},{}
6448,IssuesEvent,2018-03-17 21:27:10+00:00,39119843,miguelgrinberg/python-socketio,1800739,MyrionPhoenixmoon,,,opened,/socket.io/?EIO requests fail with 404 error,[],[],0,"The javascript Socket.IO-client seems to send some sort of keepalive message or something, automatically.
The URL used is <server:port>/socket.io/ with EIO, transport, t and sid as parameters. Unfortunately, I haven't found any documentation about what this actually is.
When used with the node-based server, this works, but with the Python server it returns 404s. 

I'm using eventlet and Flask, as in the example from the documentation:

`if __name__ == '__main__':
    # wrap Flask application with socket.io's middleware
    app = socketio.Middleware(sio, app)

    # deploy as an eventlet WSGI server
    eventlet.wsgi.server(eventlet.listen(('', 9091)), app)`",{},{}
6455,IssuesEvent,2015-07-06 19:54:45+00:00,3256774,pmclanahan/django-celery-email,19934,pmclanahan,,,closed,HTML only emails sent as plain text,[],[],3,"Messages with content_subtype overridden to ""html"" are sent as plain text when passing through djcelery.

It's because in the serialization process (email_to_dict function), only some attributes are copied. 

Fix in https://github.com/pmclanahan/django-celery-email/pull/17",{},{}
6474,IssuesEvent,2017-09-15 17:05:18+00:00,1757853,AndrewIngram/django-extra-views,1990439,bodgerbarnett,,,opened,Adding a form to a formset,[],[],0,"Is it possible to add form to a model formset?

I've got a ModelFormSetView which renders a bunch of forms for my model - but I want to add a single extra form at the bottom of the formset which will enable the user to say yes or no to something that applies to the logic of the entire page (whether to send an email about the changes).

I've tried inheriting from FormMixin but I think I must have missed something as it doesn't work.

Any ideas?",{},{}
6487,IssuesEvent,2018-08-28 18:06:47+00:00,49422756,chrisjbillington/inotify_simple,3694715,mgoldshteyn,,,opened,Performance of inotify_simple,[],[],0,"There are several pythonic ways that the performance of inotify_simple could be increased. It is hard to say by how much, without actually trying. Would you be open to such changes via a pull request or do I need to create a whole new package based on yours?",{},{}
6490,IssuesEvent,2015-01-10 18:57:20+00:00,11621778,danialfarid/angular-file-upload,7402112,paulcwarren,,,closed,Content-Type not supported,[],[],9,"Hi there,

I have same requirements as described in:-
https://github.com/danialfarid/angular-file-upload/issues/88

Using version 2.1.1

Code is pretty simple, as follows.

In my html I have:-
```
<script src=""/js/angular-file-upload/angular-file-upload-shim.js""></script>
<script src=""/js/angular-file-upload/angular-file-upload.js""></script>

<input type=""file"" ng-file-select ng-file-change=""onFileSelect($files, $event)"" />
<button class=""btn"" ng-click=""flip()"">Flip</button>
```

In my backend controller, I have:-
```
$scope.onFileSelect = function($files, $event) {
	$scope.file = $files[0];
};
				
$scope.flip = function() {
	$upload.http({
		    url: '/image-flip',
		    headers: {'Content-Type': $scope.file.type},
		    file: $scope.file
	}).progress(function(evt) {
		console.log('progress: ' + parseInt(100.0 * evt.loaded / evt.total) + '% file :'+ evt.config.file.name);
	}).success(function(data) {
		console.log('file ' + config.file.name + 'is uploaded successfully. Response: ' + data)
	}).error(function(data) {
	       //error
	});
};
```
When I execute the code the request is sent with Content-Type: application/json which is obviously wrong - should be image/jpeg - and is therefore rejected by the server which is expecting image/jpeg.

There is clearly something obvious that I am missing here but I can't spot what it is.  I did try debugging through the code but always end up in the angular code that strips content-type header before sending each request.

Any help, gratefully appreciated. 

",{},{}
6497,IssuesEvent,2018-04-11 20:39:25+00:00,104230962,eamigo86/graphene-django-extras,11740026,eamigo86,,,closed,DRF 3.8 Compatibility,[],[],2,"Upgrading to the recently released [DRF 3.8.x series](http://www.django-rest-framework.org/topics/release-notes/#38x-series) broke compatibiliy with **graphene-django-extras**

In DRF 3.8, `rest_framework.compat._resolve_model` function has been removed, but it is being imported by [utils.py#L15](https://github.com/eamigo86/graphene-django-extras/blob/master/graphene_django_extras/utils.py#L15).

I don't feel like opining on the ""correct"" solution, but since `_resolve_model` is only used when Django < 1.9, then making it not only '_conditionally used_' but also '_conditionally imported_' would make sense to me.
",{},{}
6548,IssuesEvent,2018-04-27 11:36:30+00:00,115877091,jllorencetti/pytest-deadfixtures,4660275,sobolevn,,,opened,Plugin causes invalid output,[],[],0,"Hi, thanks for the awesome idea. I have found several issues using this project.

But, I have faced an issue in one of my projects.

## How it should be

I am 100% sure that I don't have any duplicates or unused fixtures.
Link to tests: https://github.com/wemake-services/wemake-django-template/blob/master/tests/test_project_generation.py
That's exactly what this plugin reports. But it does report something really strange:

```
============================= test session starts ==============================
platform linux -- Python 3.6.5, pytest-3.5.1, py-1.5.3, pluggy-0.6.0
rootdir: /home/travis/build/wemake-services/wemake-django-template, inifile: setup.cfg
plugins: isort-0.1.0, flake8-1.0.0, deadfixtures-2.0.0, cookies-0.3.0
collected 16 items                                                             
Cool, every declared fixture is being used.
You may have some duplicate fixtures:
========================= no tests ran in 0.02 seconds =========================
The command ""pipenv run python -m pytest"" exited with 0.
```

What does it mean? Are tests executed? Why `You may have some duplicate fixtures` label is shown without any items?

Link to the build: https://travis-ci.org/wemake-services/wemake-django-template/builds/371985278

## Offtopic

Are you interested in creating ""Projects using it"" section? I would be happy to submit https://github.com/wemake-services/wemake-django-template",{},{}
