6734,IssuesEvent,2017-01-31 22:54:33+00:00,2303596,iambrandontaylor/django-admin-sortable,51939,mrmachine,,,opened,Very slow on a large set of nested sortable items.,[],[],0,"We were seeing render times of ~3 minutes when trying to render the nested page with a couple thousand items grouped into a couple hundred parent items.

Profiling revealed that the vast majority of the time was in the app dirs template loader. When we enabled the cached template loader, render time sped up by ~6x, but it still takes ~30 seconds and again the vast majority of the time is now on template `render()` calls.

I suspect it's because of the way the sort view first renders its main template, which calls a template tag which renders another template, which calls another template tag in a loop (thousands of times) which renders another template.

It might be faster if we could somehow remove the render() call inside the loop across all items?",{},{}
