8821,IssuesEvent,2015-06-03 21:02:56+00:00,1446474,pypa/virtualenv,1810591,asottile,647025,pypa,opened,Result of create_bootstrap_script fails without virtualenv,[],[],0,"Here's the simplest reproduction I could come up with (the actual case is slightly more complicated in https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit.github.io/issues/52)

```python
# make.py
import io
import virtualenv

with io.open('f.py', 'w') as f:
    f.write(virtualenv.create_bootstrap_script(
        'def adjust_options(options, args):\n'
        '    args[:] = [""venv-bootstrapped""]\n',
    ))
```

```sh
# test.sh
set -ex

virtualenv --version
virtualenv venv >& /dev/null
. venv/bin/activate
pip install virtualenv >& /dev/null
python make.py
# Verify the script works when virtualenv is installed
python f.py
# Cool
rm -rf venv-bootstrapped
pip uninstall -y virtualenv
# Womp
python f.py
```

