8984,IssuesEvent,2018-02-27 23:31:35+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,723615,emmett9001,779641,Parsely,opened,No handlers could be found for logger,"[{'id': 8945343, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsely/pykafka/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]",[],0,"In many cases (such as [this one](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/issues/722#issuecomment-330232891)), PyKafka components spit out `No handlers could be found for logger` errors. This is a nuisance for a [lot](https://stackoverflow.com/q/48930612/735204) of users. Apparently it can be fixed with the [`NullHandler`](https://docs.python.org/3.1/library/logging.html#nullhandler). ",{},{}
