8993,IssuesEvent,2016-05-19 18:40:49+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,723615,emmett9001,779641,Parsely,closed,Raising configuration errors straight from `__init__()`,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsely/pykafka/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsely/pykafka/labels/in%20progress', 'name': 'in progress', 'color': 'ededed'}]",[],1,"Currently, some config parameters are only used in worker threads, and the result is that exceptions due to invalid parameters do not emerge when calling `__init__()` but only later, when the worker threads fail, and the exception is subsequently re-raised through `consume()` or `produce()`. I think the challenge here is to find a solution that provides a nicer user experience, and that also keeps validating code and worker thread code coherent.

(This was reported by @rduplain last week, but didn't get a ticket assigned yet.)",{},{}
9000,IssuesEvent,2015-10-24 08:24:37+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,4370917,xqliang,779641,Parsely,opened,Race condition when creating multi BalancedConsumer,[],[],0,"```python
    def _add_self(self):
        """"""Register this consumer in zookeeper.
        This method ensures that the number of participants is at most the
        number of partitions.
        """"""
        participants = self._get_participants()
        # NOTE: 
Race condition here
        if len(self._topic.partitions) <= len(participants):
            raise KafkaException(""Cannot add consumer: more consumers than partitions"")

        self._zookeeper.create(
            self._path_self, self._topic.name, ephemeral=True, makepath=True)
```
As shown above, [There is](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/blob/master/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py#L412) a race condition when multi processes create BalancedConsumer at the same time with the same `consumer_group`.

When a race condition occurred, the consumer instance holds [empty partition](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/blob/master/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py#L450), and the internal `_consumer ` is [not inited](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/blob/master/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py#L464). Moreover, there is no way to stop it correctly because of the [null](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/blob/master/pykafka/balancedconsumer.py#L250) `_consumer`.",{},{}
9031,IssuesEvent,2018-03-20 18:10:00+00:00,55241091,BrandwatchLtd/api_sdk,5853241,anthonybu,807036,BrandwatchLtd,opened,Race condition when read token file,[],[],0,"When multiple threads creates BWProject, system may fail to open the token file. This exception is [explicitly discarded (bwproject.py#L104)](https://github.com/BrandwatchLtd/api_sdk/blame/b7b177c6ba9bb147b4bfe1bbde08ac2164d81abf/bwproject.py#L104), which in turn causing an UnboundLocalError at run time.",{},{}
