but I also wanna create a token in my register. so, I use this function:

```
def create_token(user):
    jwt_payload_handler = api_settings.JWT_PAYLOAD_HANDLER
    jwt_encode_handler = api_settings.JWT_ENCODE_HANDLER

    payload = jwt_payload_handler(user)
    token = jwt_encode_handler(payload)

    return token
```

The problem is that I don't have an username. So, it doesn't work. :) 
I thought, if it works with the login, it should work with the register. But not. :smiley:  

Even if I wrote this ```USERNAME_FIELD = 'email'``` in my model. It always asks for a username in my ""create_token"" function. 

But second, I would like to create the token with just the _email, password, and uuid_

And third... Is the same token from my register and from my login? To make the requests, it should be the same. 


Thank you!",{},{}
9700,IssuesEvent,2016-10-29 15:44:08+00:00,15958352,GetBlimp/django-rest-framework-jwt,8628200,mabuaisha,1227237,GetBlimp,opened,Issue with JSONWebTokenSerializer,[],[],0,"I tried to call ``/api-token-auth/`` with username = 'test@test.com' password='test', the ``username_field`` of my model is represent ``email`` field so when I pass username to the api ``email`` field resolve successfully by  when I checked the ``self.initial_data`` contains the following dict :
``
{'username':
'test@test.com',
'password': 'test'
}
``
So that make the api to fail and got email is required field.

The fix for this issue is to update ``self.initial_data`` to have the right username field",{},{}
9701,IssuesEvent,2015-08-06 19:15:22+00:00,15958352,GetBlimp/django-rest-framework-jwt,946024,cgroner,1227237,GetBlimp,opened,`NotImplementedError` on accessing `request.DATA`,[],[],0,"From `django-rest-framework` v3.2, any attempts to access `request.DATA` will raise a `NotImplementedError` with the following message:

> `request.DATA` has been deprecated in favor of `request.data` since version 3.0, and has been fully removed as of version 3.2.

You can see the change [commit here](https://github.com/tomchristie/django-rest-framework/commit/f7d44dfae0d73a33373f62cf1905c10f89fcfb9e). The error originates [here in `views.py`](https://github.com/cgroner/django-rest-framework-jwt/blob/master/rest_framework_jwt/views.py#L56).

Note that the `request.data` property appears to have been added in `django-rest-framework` v3, so simply changing `request.DATA` to `request.data` may make this package incompatible with earlier versions.",{},{}
