10524,IssuesEvent,2017-04-13 12:22:31+00:00,12345160,ansible/tower-cli,1385596,AlanCoding,1507452,ansible,opened,Support managing workflow roles,"[{'id': 53464952, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ansible/tower-cli/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 128788960, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ansible/tower-cli/labels/P2', 'name': 'P2', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}]",[],0,"This should be straightforward to implement. We don't have it for the simple reason that roles were introduced in 3.0 and workflows were introduced in 3.1, and roles were not updated.",{},{}
10526,IssuesEvent,2015-09-28 17:23:21+00:00,12345160,ansible/tower-cli,1385596,AlanCoding,1507452,ansible,closed,Support command-line extra variable option handling similar to ansible-playbook,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ansible/tower-cli/labels/in%20progress', 'name': 'in progress', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ansible/tower-cli/labels/P2', 'name': 'P2', 'color': 'fbca04'}]",[],13,"Why we can't pass extra vars as arguments ? It would ease things : 

yml file as extra vars
1. Jenkins launches the build
2. Jenkins must create a file containing extra vars which will be read by tower-cli 
3. Jenkins calls tower-cli with `tower-cli job launch --job-template 18 --extra-vars ex.yml`
4. Jenkins must erease the file

VS 

inline extra vars
1. Jenkins launches the build
2. Jenkins calls tower-cli with `tower-cli job launch --job-template 18 --extra-vars test:23,site:example.com`

That's just an example, i'm sure there are better options to pass extra vars inline


",{},{}
