10807,IssuesEvent,2018-01-27 12:45:16+00:00,21303988,pycontribs/jira,102495,ssbarnea,1846087,pycontribs,reopened,jirashell missing dependency on IPython,"[{'id': 751642399, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pycontribs/jira/labels/type:documentation', 'name': 'type:documentation', 'color': 'e58106', 'default': False}]",[],4,"Hello,

although `pip install jira` installs `jirashell`, it doesn't install IPython.

Environment:
```
MacOS 10.13.1 (latest)
virtualenv, python 3.6

virtualenv-36 ~/env/py3
activate ~/env/py3/bin/activate.fish
pip install jira
...

pip show jira
Name: jira
Version: 1.0.10
...
```

What happens:
```
jirashell -s http://jira.atlassian.com
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""/Users/foo/env/py3/bin/jirashell"", line 11, in <module>
    sys.exit(main())
  File ""/Users/foo/env/py3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/jira/jirashell.py"", line 252, in main
    from IPython.frontend.terminal.embed import InteractiveShellEmbed
ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'IPython'
```

Either `pip install jira` should install automatically also IPython or it should not install jirashell and the documentation should mention it.

",{},{}
