10968,IssuesEvent,2017-11-23 20:40:42+00:00,81612762,trailofbits/manticore,31542053,ggrieco-tob,2314423,trailofbits,opened,Manticore forks into two states that correspond to the same input when you solve the constraints,[],[],0,"### OS / Environment

Distributor ID:	ArchLinux
Description:	ArchLinux
Release:	rolling-release

### Manticore version

Last revision (ce888766cd5a7947f250c0733d2429aac4587d8d)

### Python version

Python 2.7.13

### Summary of the problem

Manticore forks into two states that correspond to the same input when you solve the constraints.

### Step to reproduce the behavior

Use this example

```
from manticore import Manticore
from manticore.core.plugin import Plugin
from manticore.core.smtlib import ConstraintSet
from manticore.core.state import State
from manticore.platforms import decree


def make_symbolic_decree(program, concrete_data):

    constraints = ConstraintSet()
    platform = decree.SDecree(constraints, program)
    initial_state = State(constraints, platform)
    concrete_len = len(concrete_data)
    concrete_data[0] = '+'
    concrete_data[-1] = '+'
    concrete_data = """".join(concrete_data)

    platform.input.transmit(initial_state.symbolicate_buffer(concrete_data, wildcard='+', label='STDIN'))
    return initial_state


class StateCollector(Plugin):
    def __init__(self):
        super(StateCollector, self).__init__()

    def will_fork_state_callback(self, state, expression, solutions, policy):
        self.manticore._executor.generate_testcase(state, ""New forked state!"")

if __name__ == '__main__':
    initial_state = make_symbolic_decree
    Manticore.verbosity(1)
    m = Manticore(make_symbolic_decree(""CROMU_00001"", list(""ABCDEF"")))
    m.register_plugin(StateCollector())
    m.run()
```

using the CROMU_00001 pre-compiled CGC binary.

### Expected behavior

It shouldn't fork.

### Actual behavior

```
$ python2 symbolize.py
2017-11-23 17:26:58,803: [27063] m.manticore:INFO: Starting 1 processes.
2017-11-23 17:26:59,372: [27063] m.manticore:INFO: Generated testcase No. 0 - New forked state!
2017-11-23 17:27:00,738: [27063] m.manticore:INFO: Generated testcase No. 1 - New forked state!
^C2017-11-23 17:27:04,685: [27063] m.manticore:INFO: Results in mcore_XJF4oO
2017-11-23 17:27:04,685: [27063] m.manticore:INFO: Total time: 5.88238811493
$ ls mcore_XJF4oO/
command.sh          test_00000000.messages  test_00000000.smt    test_00000000.txt       test_00000001.pkl  test_00000001.trace  visited.txt
state_00000003.pkl  test_00000000.pkl       test_00000000.trace  test_00000001.messages  test_00000001.smt  test_00000001.txt
$ cat mcore_XJF4oO/test_*.txt
STDIN_1: '\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00'
STDIN_1: '\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00'
```",{},{}
