11149,IssuesEvent,2015-11-19 00:39:30+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python,242750,tseaver,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,Strip excess custom exceptions from 'gcloud.streaming',"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python/labels/hygiene', 'name': 'hygiene', 'color': 'bfdadc'}]",[],0,"Many (all, maybe) of the custom exception types in `gcloud.streaming.exceptions` are providing no value, and could be replaced with either standard exceptions (`ValueError`, `TypeError`, etc.), or one of our existing types mapping particular HTTP response codes.

Strip out as many of the custom types as seems feasible, and move the remainder to `gcloud.exceptions`.",{},{}
11164,IssuesEvent,2015-05-29 21:41:47+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/gcloud-python,250995,jonparrott,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,Not possible to set the datastore namespace globally.,[],[],0,"Currently, ``gcloud.datastore.set_defaults`` lets you set the default dataset id, but doesn't let you set the default namespace. This means to use a namespace you have to be meticulous about setting in in every query, key, etc. 

