11252,IssuesEvent,2018-06-07 22:04:35+00:00,16316451,GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python,1907648,frankyn,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,opened,[Storage] make_public() and public_url() don't describe how they work/when they work.,"[{'id': 77678602, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw3NzY3ODYwMg==', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/GoogleCloudPlatform/google-cloud-python/labels/api:%20storage', 'name': 'api: storage', 'color': 'f8f8f8', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Documentation for `make_public()` and `public_url()` don't describe how they work/when they work.

Specifically `make_public()` uses ACLs to make the object public and `public_url()` only works when the object has necessary permissions granted to all users in the form of `ACL` or a bucket has an IAM policy assigning `allUsers` the role `roles/storage.objectViewer`.

(noting this down as I don't want to forget it.)",{},{}
