11874,IssuesEvent,2016-11-01 06:38:40+00:00,13592924,python-openxml/python-docx,2062718,scanny,3403760,python-openxml,closed,Iterating over table.row_cells returns creates copies of cell objects,[],[],1,"First, thanks for this package! Please take a look at the object addresses when iterating over row_cells. Why do the addresses keep changing? Looks like a copy is being created each time. Why? This doesn't seem intuitive.

```python
Iterate over the cells in row 58.
>>> for c in t.row_cells(58):
	print(c)
<docx.table._Cell object at 0x0000000003A710B8>
<docx.table._Cell object at 0x00000000039D3CC0>
<docx.table._Cell object at 0x0000000003A6F8D0>
<docx.table._Cell object at 0x0000000003A6F908>


c = t.row_cells(58)[0]
c.text = 'blah'
t.row_cells(58)[0].text
''

I would expect cell 0 of row 58 to contain 'blah'

Iterate again.

>>> for c in t.row_cells(58):
	print(c)
<docx.table._Cell object at 0x0000000003A6F828>
<docx.table._Cell object at 0x0000000003A6F860>
<docx.table._Cell object at 0x0000000003A6F898>
<docx.table._Cell object at 0x0000000003A6F940>
