 - Operating system: Android 6.0.1 (on Samsung S5)
 - Browser: n/a (Android App)

## How to reproduce

1. Install Android App
2. Import Channel ID (I was using 93a5bfcfa2a74962be843288aefcfc0e)
3. Wait a while for it to finish loading. See if you ultimately get the error screen.
4. Close out of the app and re-enter the app. See if the content was successfully loaded.

## Screenshots

![screenshot_2017-06-15-19-46-36](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25990164/27206774-8d1c3a52-5207-11e7-8e25-a3eeb229a207.png)
![screenshot_2017-06-15-19-51-39](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25990164/27206772-874729e8-5207-11e7-94f8-0fc7997deed2.png)

## Real-life consequences (anything community should be aware of, for instance how it affects your deployment)

It's useful to know when the content has finished being imported. I could see many partners being troubled by this.",{},{}
12061,IssuesEvent,2018-06-22 20:49:30+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,7193975,christianmemije,3926525,learningequality,closed,Simple login screen language dropdown causes layout issues,"[{'id': 492821376, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0OTI4MjEzNzY=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/DEV:%20frontend', 'name': 'DEV: frontend', 'color': 'DFDFDF', 'default': False}, {'id': 667034929, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw2NjcwMzQ5Mjk=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/learningequality/kolibri/labels/P2%20-%20normal', 'name': 'P2 - normal', 'color': 'ffba00', 'default': False}]",[],4,"### Observed behavior
On the new simple login screen, the language dropdown behaves a bit strange, to say the least. I've tested the issue on Chrome and Firefox, running on Ubuntu 17.10.

#### Chrome
- version: 65.0.3325.181 (Official Build) (64-bit), 66.0.3359.170 (Official Build) (64-bit)
- description: It makes the entire language footer jump up.
- screencast gif: 

![kolibribeta-peek-chrome](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2150991/39999790-4f91adaa-578a-11e8-923c-e823ef117d5c.gif)

#### Firefox
- version: 59.0.2 (64-bit)
- description: 
  - if I click on the ""More languages"" text, dropdown jumps down and browser gets a vertical scroll
  - if I click on the caret icon, dropdown jumps down, but there is no vertical scroll so it's actually impossible to select anything
- screencast gif: 

![kolibribeta-peek-ff](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2150991/39999931-bc055c34-578a-11e8-8200-a1ed3345c46e.gif)

### Expected behavior
I would maybe expect the dropdown to jump up, I believe that would resolved the described issue.

### User-facing consequences
Mostly inconvinience with regards to the content jumping and vertical scroll, but in some cases also the inability to select a language from the dropdown (if the caret icon is clicked on Firefox).

### Errors and logs
n/a

### Steps to reproduce
Visit http://kolibridemo.learningequality.org.

### Context
 * Kolibri version: version which is deployed on http://kolibridemo.learningequality.org
 * Operating system: Ubuntu 17.10
 * Browser: 
    * Chrome: 65.0.3325.181 (Official Build) (64-bit), 66.0.3359.170 (Official Build) (64-bit)
    * Firefox: 59.0.2 (64-bit)
",{},{}
