```
As I understand it, the error at line 159 of BayesianModel.py is thrown because 'a' and 'c' are not variables in the BayesianModel constructed on line 88 in base.py, which is initialised with an empty array returned from `get_intra_edges(0)`.

I've tried making sure the variables are present prior to adding the CPDs, but that just results in related errors further down. So I'm not quite sure how best to approach fixing this, or whether I am doing something wrong?

Cheers,
