12574,IssuesEvent,2017-10-25 19:42:30+00:00,91020334,ni/nimi-python,8085768,marcoskirsch,5598284,ni,closed,NI-FAKE GetAStringWithSpecifiedMaximumSize function is invalid,"[{'id': 656403855, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ni/nimi-python/labels/test', 'name': 'test', 'color': 'f9d0c4', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'marcoskirsch', 'id': 8085768, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/8085768?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/marcoskirsch', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/marcoskirsch', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/marcoskirsch/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/marcoskirsch/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/marcoskirsch/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/marcoskirsch/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/marcoskirsch/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/marcoskirsch/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/marcoskirsch/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/marcoskirsch/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/marcoskirsch/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"We have some unit tests in NI-FAKE for a function GetAStringWithSpecifiedMaximumSize:

    niFake_GetAStringWithSpecifiedMaximumSize(ViSession, ViChar*, ViInt32);

The corresponding Session method:

    def get_a_string_with_specified_maximum_size(self, buffer_size):

The C user is supposed to pass a buffer and the max size of the buffer. In Python, the buffer_size is exposed. This makes no sense from the Python API point of view. Clients should never have to deal with string memory allocation.

Recommendation is to remove the function. There are other unit tests in which the function is used for different reasons - a different function should be used in those.",{},{}
