12645,IssuesEvent,2018-08-20 06:17:11+00:00,91356408,allenai/allennlp,12494156,iamyihwa,5667695,allenai,opened,ELMO in PyTorch? ,[],[],0,"**Describe the bug**
I am implementing a Spanish NER using AllenNLP.
As a first attempt, I have used elmo_token_embedder as in ner-es.jsonnet. 
However since it is a different language, it might make more sense to train ELMO. 
I only find the way to train ELMO using Tensorflow ([here](https://github.com/allenai/bilm-tf)).
However I am wondering if so, it is later reusable on AllenNLP which has PyTorch backend. 



**To Reproduce**
