13049,IssuesEvent,2015-05-12 17:03:01+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,4573865,orodbhen,6392739,conda,opened,option to install from source,[],[],0,"It would be useful to provide a conda install option that recompiles the package(s) before installing. Similar to what pip does.

Expecting a single binary package to run on any platform is a little overly ambitious in some cases. This might work OK for Python packages, but for conda to be a means of installing any package into a  semi self-contained environment, I think it really needs to have this capability. 

It seems like this would be failry simple to implement. Just download the package, extract the recipe, and go. Unfortunately, in the case of many Anaconda packages, this won't work because the recipes are in the wrong format. Moreover, it's pretty wasteful to do it this way, and it would be better to only download the recipe files before running conda build.",{},{}
