13216,IssuesEvent,2017-06-04 18:04:17+00:00,83561095,wildfoundry/dataplicity-lomond,5367846,larsenglund,6545066,wildfoundry,opened,TypeError in message.py,[],[],0,"Hi, I tried installing dataplicity on my raspberry pi but I couldn't connect. A look in the log, `less /var/log/dataplicity.log`, showed the same error over and over again:
```
  File ""/home/dataplicity/.pex/install/lomond-0.1.7a0-py2.py3-none-any.whl.f9cee7ed31f72b160ca023b6fcbe37bc4b1726ef/lomond-0.1.7a0-py2.py3-none-any.whl/lomond/message.py"", line 20, in Message
    _unpack16 = struct.Struct('!H').unpack
TypeError: Struct() argument 1 must be string, not unicode
```
I fixed this by changing line 20 in message.py from `_unpack16 = struct.Struct('!H').unpack` to `_unpack16 = struct.Struct('!H'.encode('utf-8')).unpack` and after restarting dataplicity with `sudo supervisorctl restart tuxtunnel` I was able to connect successfully. I just thought I would post this here if someone else has the same problem with dataplicity. ",{},{}
