13354,IssuesEvent,2016-10-24 22:28:52+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,16448634,derekbekoe,6844498,Azure,opened,Cannot use storage data-plane commands with other clouds,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/Storage', 'name': 'Storage', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}]",[],0,"Due to a bug in azure-storage (https://github.com/Azure/azure-storage-python/issues/229), using storage data-plane commands with a different cloud will hang/not terminate.

Repro with:
1. Point the CLI to a different cloud.
2. `export AZURE_STORAGE_CONNECTION_STRING=""DefaultEndpointsProtocol=https;AccountName=<account_name>;AccountKey=<account_key>""`
3. `az storage container list --debug`

The Azure Storage SDK will attempt to connect to <account_name>.blob.core.windows.net instead of using the correct endpoint suffix for the cloud.

When the issue is fixed in the SDK, it can be verified in the CLI.",{},{}
