13396,IssuesEvent,2017-01-25 23:26:23+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,5723682,tjprescott,6844498,Azure,closed,az vm create: --vnet docs conflict,"[{'id': 418936879, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/Compute', 'name': 'Compute', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}, {'id': 418968915, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/Discussion', 'name': 'Discussion', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'vishrutshah', 'id': 8782776, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8782776?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vishrutshah', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/vishrutshah', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vishrutshah/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vishrutshah/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vishrutshah/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vishrutshah/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vishrutshah/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vishrutshah/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vishrutshah/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vishrutshah/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vishrutshah/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",5,"`az vm create -h` says:

```
    --vnet                        : Name or ID of virtual network (creates if doesn't exist).
                                    Chooses an existing VNet if none specified.
```

and a few lines below it says (note the `to an existing Virtual Network` part)

```
    Create a Linux VM with SSH key authentication, add a public DNS entry and add to an existing
    Virtual Network and Availability Set.
        az vm create -n my_vm_name -g myrg --image <linux image from 'az vm image list'>
        --authentication-type ssh --vnet my_existing_vnet --subnet-name subnet1 --availability-set
        my_existing_availability_set --public-ip-address-dns-name my_globally_unique_vm_dns_name
        --ssh-key-value ""<ssh-rsa-key, key-file-path or not specified for default-key-path>""
```

It sounds like the latter statement is a bit less accurate.
",{},{}
