13426,IssuesEvent,2018-03-27 20:39:20+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,5723682,tjprescott,6844498,Azure,opened,[BatchAI] Issues to resolve prior to GA,"[{'id': 732002650, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/BatchAI', 'name': 'BatchAI', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}, {'id': 419034377, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/Fit&Finish', 'name': 'Fit&Finish', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Applicable to PR #5923.

**cluster**

- [ ] needs `--ids` support for `delete`, `show`, `list-files`, `list-nodes`
- [ ] `create`: issues with non-standard behavior list extra resource group arguments, arguments that only support name or only support ID.
- [ ] `resize` and `auto-scale` should be folded into a single `update` command which supports the generic update parameter.

**usage**
- [ ] Only has a single command. This should be hyphenated and upleveled to `az batchai show-usage` unless there will be other usage commands.

**job**
- [ ] `wait` is not using the infrastructure's generic wait pattern.
- [ ] `--ids` should be supported for a number of commands.
- [ ] `create` requires a JSON file.
- [ ] `create` seems to duplicate many of the parameters of `cluster create` and thus has the same issues regarding extra resource group parameters.
- [ ] `list-files`: `output-directory-id` isn't clear and has a random short option (no short option is likely appropriate here).
- [ ] `terminate`: the verb `stop` has precedent in the CLI and should probably be used here
- [ ] `stream-file`: has different naming/aliasing from `list-files`.  These two commands could go into a subcommand as `list` and `stream` respectively.

**file-servers**
- [ ] `create`: Subnet should support names or ID (which means exposing an optional vnet-name argument).
- [ ] `--ids` should be supported
- [ ] Missing generic update command
",{},{}
