13828,IssuesEvent,2017-01-11 17:37:00+00:00,23984796,jupyter/nbgrader,83444,jhamrick,7388996,jupyter,closed,Working with assignment/student from the command line,"[{'id': 129124230, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jupyter/nbgrader/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],6,"It used to be that nbgrader could automatically create assignments and students from running the various command line stages. That was removed, with the recommendation for instructors to edit their `nbgrader_config.py`. However, we are moving to a model where that file gets read only when JupyterHub itself is started (which would force the restarting of JupyterHub to add students/assignments) or when the single user notebook server is restarted (which would force that to be restarted).

I propose that for the upcoming release we add a lightweight command line way of managing assignments and students. Something like this:

```
$ nbgrader students add bsimpson --full-name ""Bart Simpson""
# nbgrader students import students.csv # in some standard format
$ nbgrader assignment add assignment01 --due-date=""...""
```

These commands shouldn't be too difficult and would relieve instructors from needing to work with the db through the Python API. This would really help the usability as we migrate first to formgrade being a service and then a serverextension.

@jhamrick ",{},{}
