14942,IssuesEvent,2018-05-09 10:59:32+00:00,43816051,common-workflow-language/cwltool,6304200,ThomasHickman,9947495,common-workflow-language,opened,Caching fails to work properly when using the same dockerised tool in different steps,[],[],0,"https://github.com/common-workflow-language/cwltool/blob/9e3e720ffc18ade0a19fdbb2bea1bed25e9662ae/cwltool/command_line_tool.py#L299-L302

This uses self.requirement and self.hints, which are mutated when a tool is run:

https://github.com/common-workflow-language/cwltool/blob/9e3e720ffc18ade0a19fdbb2bea1bed25e9662ae/cwltool/docker.py#L39-L40

If a workflow uses the same tool multiple times, whether a cache hit occurs for a step will depend on whether the same tool has been run before or not.

## Example

### Inputs

<details><summary>test_workflow.cwl</summary>
<p>

    #!/usr/bin/env cwl-runner

    cwlVersion: v1.0
    class: Workflow

    inputs: []
    outputs: []

    steps:
    task1:
        run: test_tool.cwl
        in:
        message:
            default: one
        out: []
    task2:
        run: test_tool.cwl
        in:
        message:
            default: two
        out: []
</p>
</details>

<details><summary>test_tool.cwl</summary>
<p>

    #!/usr/bin/env cwl-runner

    cwlVersion: v1.0
    class: CommandLineTool
    baseCommand: touch
    requirements:
    DockerRequirement:
        dockerPull: alpine
    inputs:
    message:
        type: string
        inputBinding:
        position: 1
    outputs:
    - id: out
        type: File
        outputBinding:
        glob: ""*""
</p>
</details>

