15025,IssuesEvent,2017-04-11 00:40:51+00:00,27610253,ubyssey/dispatch,2547035,psiemens,10091792,ubyssey,opened,Write unit tests for Pages endpoints,[],"[{'login': 'Axel-Jacobsen', 'id': 20530172, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/20530172?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Axel-Jacobsen', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/Axel-Jacobsen', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Axel-Jacobsen/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Axel-Jacobsen/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Axel-Jacobsen/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Axel-Jacobsen/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Axel-Jacobsen/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Axel-Jacobsen/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Axel-Jacobsen/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Axel-Jacobsen/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Axel-Jacobsen/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"We need to add a test suite to cover the `api/pages/` endpoint.

You can use this file as an example for how to structure the tests: https://github.com/ubyssey/dispatch/blob/develop/dispatch/tests/test_api_articles.py

The `api/pages/` endpoint supports the following methods:

```py
# List all pages
GET api/pages/

# Retrieve a specific page
GET api/pages/{page_id}/

# Create a new page
POST api/pages/

# Update an existing page
PATCH api/pages/{page_id}/

# Delete a page
DELETE api/pages/{page_id}/
```

When making a `POST` or `PATCH` request, the request body should look something like this:

```json
{
  ""title"": ""Test Page"",
  ""slug"": ""test-page"",
  ""snippet"": ""This is a test snippet"",
  ""content"": [
    {
      ""type"": ""paragraph"",
      ""data"": ""This is some paragraph text""
    },
    {
      ""type"": ""paragraph"",
      ""data"": ""This is another paragraph""
    }
  ]
}
```

Here are the test cases we should cover (if you think of more, please add them!):

- Attempting to create a page while unauthorized should result in 401
- Attempting to delete a page while unauthorized should result in 401
- Attempting to create a page without any of the required fields (title, slug, content) should result in 400
- Attempting to create a page with an empty request (`data=None or data={}`) should result in 400
- Should be able to create a page 
- Should be able to update the basic fields of a page (title, slug, snippet)
- Should be able to update the content of a page
- Should be able to delete an existing page",{},{}
