15583,IssuesEvent,2017-11-28 17:34:54+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,3085284,NikolajBjorner,11668813,Z3Prover,closed,Recursive functions: Z3 doesn't terminate,[],[],0,"This is a variant on #1370, but the script is even simpler in a sense since the recursive call is made with smaller arguments in `(computeSize 1 1)`:

```
(declare-fun items ()  (Array Int Int))

(assert (= (select items 1) 4))
(assert (= (select items 2) 4))

(define-fun-rec computeSize ((lb Int) (ub Int)) Int
   (ite (> lb ub)
        0
        (+ (select items lb)
           (computeSize (+ lb 1) ub))))

(define-fun totalSize () Int (computeSize 1 1))
(assert (> totalSize 1))

(check-sat)
(get-value (totalSize))
```

When I run it, I get:

```
sat
^C
```

That is, the `get-value` call never terminates. Looking at the processes, it seems Z3 is simply chugging away at 100% CPU utilization.",{},{}
