15785,IssuesEvent,2018-06-14 16:59:18+00:00,37496521,nteract/nteract,3758694,nickynicolson,12401040,nteract,opened,Installation requires jupyter serverextension enable...,[],[],0,"Installation instructions in the [nteract_on_jupyter article](https://blog.nteract.io/nteract-on-jupyter-53cc2c38290d) suggest that these steps would be sufficient:

    pip install nteract_on_jupyter
    jupyter nteract

In my environment (Python 3.6.1 :: Anaconda custom (64-bit), jupyter version 4.3.0, nteract_on_jupyter version 1.7.0) this starts a notebook server, spawns a browser at http://localhost:8888/nteract/edit which displays a 404
If I do:

    jupyter serverextension enable nteract
    jupyter nteract

... then all is well.

@rgbkrk thought that use of jupyter config.d would make this enable automatically (i.e. render the serverextension command redundant)",{},{}
