16064,IssuesEvent,2016-03-11 11:53:05+00:00,16469697,mps-youtube/mps-youtube,3929903,Vrihub,12987682,mps-youtube,opened,album matching should use album title information,[],[],0,"
In the ""matching"" step of the `album` command, it seems that mpsyt only uses each individual song's title to search for videos, without also using the album title. This can lead to wrong results, in the common case when the same song appears on different albums by the same artist.

e.g. search for `album four and more`, mpsyt will correctly suggest the ""Four and More"" live album by Miles Davis, but if you then proceed to the ""matching"" step, mpsyt will download versions of the songs appearing on studio albums, or TV appearances, not the songs actually contained in the ""Four and More"" album, which are in fact available on youtube (if you run `/four and more miles davis` you can see them).

It seems that mpsyt looks for videos only using the song title and artist name, while in fact it should also use the album title to get the correct song versions.",{},{}
16074,IssuesEvent,2018-06-23 19:37:24+00:00,51397392,pytroll/satpy,1828519,djhoese,13004956,pytroll,opened,Non-requested datasets are saved when composites fail to generate,"[{'id': 865017416, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw4NjUwMTc0MTY=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/satpy/labels/component:scene', 'name': 'component:scene', 'color': '1d76db', 'default': False}, {'id': 751601587, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw3NTE2MDE1ODc=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/satpy/labels/good%20first%20issue', 'name': 'good first issue', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': True}, {'id': 323805265, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwzMjM4MDUyNjU=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pytroll/satpy/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '159818', 'default': True}]",[],0,"**Describe the bug**

Right now the `Scene` objects `save_datasets` method defaults to saving **all** currently loaded/existing datasets. This means that if a composite hasn't been generated yet, either by `generate=False` or IncompatibleAreas or some unexpected failure then `scn.save_datasets()` will save dependency datasets that weren't actually requested by the user. This can be very confusing.

**To Reproduce**

```python
scn = Scene(reader='abi_l1b', filenames=[...])
scn.load(['true_color'])
scn.save_datasets()

```

**Expected behavior**

Only true_color would be saved if it exists or it won't be saved. Optionally it could raise an exception if *none* of the requested datasets (`Scene.wishlist`) are available to save.

**Actual results**

C01, C02, C03, etc. geotiffs will be saved.

**Screenshots**
If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem.

**Environment Info:**
 - OS: [e.g. OSX, Windows, Linux]
 - SatPy Version: [e.g. 0.9.0]
 - PyResample Version: 

**Additional context**
Add any other context about the problem here.
",{},{}
16094,IssuesEvent,2017-03-13 07:44:28+00:00,1962269,django-webtest/django-webtest,118673,gawel,13016086,django-webtest,closed,Factory method to get a new `app` object,[],[],8,"Thanks for the project! I have a quick feature request. Perhaps there is a way to do it already... It would be nice to have a factory method to get a new `app` object that is set up the same way as the `self.app` object.

I often have to check that two users can interact in a sane way (user A creates an object, user B can view it) and my functional test would need two logged in users. In these cases I use `self.app` for one of them, and would need to set up a second one because the session is tied to `self.app.session` but I want them to be set up identically (and with all of the nice things) django-webtest provides.

