16254,IssuesEvent,2016-09-01 08:57:51+00:00,31315021,Kinto/kinto,229453,Natim,13413813,Kinto,closed,Support for filtering records based on a text search,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Kinto/kinto/labels/protocol', 'name': 'protocol', 'color': 'bfe5bf'}]",[],3,"As discussed originally [here](http://kinto.readthedocs.io/en/stable/api/1.x/filtering.html#comment-2858589565), I believe there needs to be some basic support for filtering based on text search on a string field. -- something like `?in_myStringField=foo` matching any records where `myStringField` is `LIKE '%foo%'`

I understand that one, can add elastic-search plugin to benefit from full-text search plus many other things it supports, but that sounds like a long way to go if all you need is to build a simple CRUD application with standard text search.",{},{}
