16517,IssuesEvent,2016-02-09 18:19:49+00:00,43852872,PulpQE/pulp-smash,1012989,Ichimonji10,14839747,PulpQE,closed,Test that Docker images can be synced from the v2 registry,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/PulpQE/pulp-smash/labels/high%20priority', 'name': 'high priority', 'color': 'e11d21'}]",[],1,"1. Use `registry-1.docker.io` as your feed url.
2. ""Upstream name"" must be in the format <namespace>/<reponame>. For repos that do not have a namespace, use ""library"". See: https://pulp.plan.io/issues/1404

Steps

1. Create a docker repo with feed registry-1.docker.io

    pulp-admin docker repo create --repo-id=synctest --feed=https://registry-1.docker.io --upstream-    name=library/busybox

    Assert:  Repository create is successful

2. Synchronize the repository

    pulp-admin docker repo sync run --repo-id synctest

    Assert: Docker images are synced

",{},{}
