17201,IssuesEvent,2016-08-03 21:20:35+00:00,53549881,anymail/django-anymail,639984,medmunds,17517617,anymail,closed,Consider including esp_extra to EmailMultiAlternatives example in Anymail 1-2-3,[],[],2,"The Anymail 1-2-3 document example is for Mailgun, but it does not directly address Mailgun's suggestion of using a subdomain to send mail:

""_We recommend using a subdomain with Mailgun, like “mg.mydomain.com”. Using a subdomain you will still be able to send emails from your root domain e.g. “you@mydomain.com”._""

Anymail does support this setting via [esp_extra](https://anymail.readthedocs.io/en/latest/esps/mailgun/), but the example using EmailMultiAlternatives does not demonstrate the use of this.

Since the recommendation from mailgun is to use a subdomain, I recommend adding a line, 

`msg.esp_extra = {""sender_domain"": ""example.com""}, # change to mg.example.com or other subdomain if necessary.` 

which demonstrates how to manually set this. This helps avoid a potential [beginner stumbling block](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/37375532/mailgun-domain-not-found-abc-com/38058296).",{},{}
17226,IssuesEvent,2016-12-09 15:02:22+00:00,38581626,pybind/pybind11,13848742,KerstinKeller,17565521,pybind,opened,Allow proper Cmake installation,[],[],0,"Hi,

I am new to bybind11, it seams great so far! But I have one question about actually installing pybind11 with cmake instead of adding it as a `add_subdirectory(pybind11)`.

The goal for me is to once install pybind11 and then use it from anywhere on my system by simply adding:

    find_package(pybind11 REQUIRED)
    pybind11_add_module(something.cpp)

From reading the CMakeLists.txt file, this is not possible at the moment.
If the option `PYBIND11_INSTALL` is set, then all headers are installed to `include/pybind11`. While this is part of the solution, shouldn't also the functions `pybind11_add_module` and `pybind11_enable_warnings` be installed too?

This would require to move them to a different file (e.g. pybind11Functions.cmake) and also create a bybind11Config.cmake file, which is installed, too. It sets `PYBIND11_INCLUDE_DIR` and includes pybind11Functions.cmake.

What do you think about this issue?
",{},{}
17250,IssuesEvent,2017-07-11 19:10:07+00:00,38581626,pybind/pybind11,10697990,tkoch96,17565521,pybind,closed,Passing arguments when calling python functions,[],[],4,"Hello,

