17584,IssuesEvent,2017-09-13 16:18:56+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,3705643,konradkonrad,19666847,raiden-network,opened,EventTransferSentSuccess should contain `amount` and `target`,[],[],0,"## Problem Definition

Currently `EventTransferSentSuccess` events are only informative, if the user keeps an out-of-band book over all initiated transfers and their respective identifiers. I.e.

`{""event_type"": ""EventTransferSentSuccess"", ""identifier"": 123456}`

does not allow to learn anything about the details of the transfer.

## Solution

`EventTransferSentSuccess` should mirror `EventTransferReceivedSuccess` and contain the fields
- `amount`
- `target`
as well.


## Tasklist

- [ ] Add `amount` and `target` to `EventTransferSentSuccess`
- [ ] Add tests for correct values for these fields
- [ ] Adjust the API endpoint, specs & docs to include these
- [ ] Adjust the `webui` implementation to make use of these",{},{}
17596,IssuesEvent,2017-03-24 11:24:35+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,1026799,czepluch,19666847,raiden-network,closed,Get rid of the incremental nonce check in NettingChannelLibrary,"[{'id': 516858058, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/2', 'name': '2', 'color': 'FFA500', 'default': False}, {'id': 318426945, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 473052392, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/mvp_protocol', 'name': 'mvp_protocol', 'color': 'b60205', 'default': False}, {'id': 559644825, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/raiden-network/raiden/labels/sprint_6', 'name': 'sprint_6', 'color': '000000', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'czepluch', 'id': 1026799, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/1026799?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/czepluch', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/czepluch', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/czepluch/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/czepluch/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/czepluch/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/czepluch/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/czepluch/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/czepluch/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/czepluch/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/czepluch/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/czepluch/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",12,"Thanks to @stonecoldpat an issue was found with the incremental nonce check in [NettingChannelLibrary](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/b14085c39c243d1684f0ddbed229abdac21e8229/raiden/smart_contracts/NettingChannelLibrary.sol#L274). 

In the case of a courtesy close a malicious Alice can provide a 0 value transfer for her latest transfer as the second argument to the `close()` function that has the maximum int value for the nonce.

This would render Bob unable to use `updateTransfer()` since any transaction would throw due to the `transfer.nonce` already having the maximum value.

The aforementioned check makes no sense anymore and should be removed. Some other requirements (explained below) haveto also be implemented along with the nonce check removal. This is an issue to implement:

### TODO

- [x] **Remove the [nonce check](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/b14085c39c243d1684f0ddbed229abdac21e8229/raiden/smart_contracts/NettingChannelLibrary.sol#L274)**

It currently serves no purpose other than making sure every transfer submitted is newer compared to the previous ones. When you close by providing the counterparty's transfer you are incentivized to provide the latest transfer anyway since it will contain the biggest transferred amount.

- [x] **Make sure that `updateTransfer()` can only be called once**
- [x] **Get Rid of the courtesy close**
Even though this is just a courtesy, it makes little sense and should be done away with.
Instead some sort of cooperative close (https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/issues/217) should be implemented in its place",{},{}
17604,IssuesEvent,2017-08-16 15:42:20+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,1658405,LefterisJP,19666847,raiden-network,closed,Make sure all calls to the ethereum node happen from the node address,[],"[{'login': 'LefterisJP', 'id': 1658405, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/1658405?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/LefterisJP', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/LefterisJP', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/LefterisJP/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/LefterisJP/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/LefterisJP/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/LefterisJP/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/LefterisJP/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/LefterisJP/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/LefterisJP/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/LefterisJP/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/LefterisJP/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"## Problem
If you are using `geth` (presumably also parity) and not using `eth.accounts[0]` as your raiden node address then since not all calls from raiden have the `from` properly specified, then all calls that rely on `msg.sender` are going to be wrong.

## To Do

Make sure that in the rpc/client.py all calls are made with `from` adrress set to our raiden node's address.",{},{}
17608,IssuesEvent,2018-08-09 12:00:42+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,40204055,BCsRock,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Raiden gets stuck in Update NonClosing balance proof transaction,[],[],0,"Hi guys, 

tl;dr:
this could be a bug in case an account joins a payment channel with zero Ethereum or having not enough funds to pay the update / settlement transactions. It seems to run into a stucked state with a repeatedly failing transaction. 

Find debug.log file further below. 

## Problem Definition

Following scenario was tested :

Acc1 had some ERC20 token and some Ethereum
Acc2 had no ERC20 token and no Ethereum

Acc1 registered ERC20 token as Raiden payment channel network, opened a channel with Acc2, deployed a deposit, sent some ERC20 token off-chain to Acc2. 
All of this was successful. 

Then, Acc1 called a settlement which caused a transaction to be mined -> was successful. 

Then Acc2 should have called a transaction but this failed due to low gas error. 

Then Acc1 sent on-chain some ethereum to Acc2. 

Restarting Raiden client with Acc2 tries to make `Update Nonclosing balance proof transaction`  transaction, but fails with error message below:

```
Update NonClosing balance proof transaction threw. Receipt=AttributeDict({'blockHash': HexBytes('0x79c90b22f969b6d7b0067a9ba068519c8559ae453e980e311d21861436f28d09'), 'blockNumber': 3801406, 'contractAddress': None, 'cumulativeGasUsed': 1156498, 'gasUsed': 96119, 'logs': [], 'logsBloom': HexBytes(''), 'root': None, 'status': 0, 'transactionHash': HexBytes('0x07416563ae15729a7c7b76048f5e69428866accd495231ee4bbf3135a4de525a'), 'transactionIndex': 15})
```

The raiden-deub.log can be found via [gist record](https://gist.github.com/BCsRock/1c0ad7ede501760c6c6a454033712b69#file-180809-raiden-debug-log). 

The ever failing transactions from restarting Acc2 can be found for example [here ](https://ropsten.etherscan.io/tx/0x6e3a03b1438a759e800f1a4a6aa8bcc7d5bbca67517e499221afce88f182ee51) or [here ](https://ropsten.etherscan.io/tx/0x6e3a03b1438a759e800f1a4a6aa8bcc7d5bbca67517e499221afce88f182ee51)

Now the problem is, the channel is officially in the state `closed` but I can neither send any Tokens between Acc1 and Acc2. Acc1 has received the correct balance from the off-chain transfers, but Acc2 did not receive a balance. I can also not re-open the channel, because it already exists. If I see correctly, the ERC20 tokens for Acc2 are frozen in the smart contract which I cannot settle / update. 

### System Description

```
Ubuntu 16.04 LTC
Raiden-0.4.2
Parity/v1.10.6-unstable-bc0d134-20180605/x86_64-linux-gnu/rustc1.26.2
```
",{},{}
