17668,IssuesEvent,2017-07-10 03:34:34+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,closed,Report used resource.,"[{'id': 325435539, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/request', 'name': 'request', 'color': '159818', 'default': False}]",[],6,"Resource used by workflow is now reported immediately after a step is completed and is scattered around under `.sos`. Now that we have an unique ID for each run, we should be able to create a master index to collect such information and report resource used, possibly using a plot. This is helpful to, for example, determine resource used and update the workflow with proper `walltime` option so that it can run better on cluster.
",{},{}
17671,IssuesEvent,2017-03-07 15:43:33+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,opened,Support for task engine in interactive mode.,"[{'id': 325435539, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/request', 'name': 'request', 'color': '159818', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'BoPeng', 'id': 9889312, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/9889312?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/BoPeng', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"We have merged single-process, multi-process and dryrun workflow executor but it appears infeasible to use batch mode executor for interactive use. The biggest problem is that interactive executor uses a single process that shares all variables so that variables would be persistent across multiple cells. This is fundamentally different from the batch mode.

We should however enhance the interactive executor for it to support task engines so that we can submit jobs from the jupyter notebook interface. This should however be implemented after the tasks can be really separated from the sos process so that sos can exit without killing the running jobs (remaining of #448).",{},{}
17673,IssuesEvent,2017-02-22 02:33:42+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,917985,gaow,20074389,vatlab,closed,An option to hide stdout / stderr from actions,"[{'id': 325435539, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/request', 'name': 'request', 'color': '159818', 'default': False}]",[],4,Sometimes we run into software packages (particularly in R) where the authors prints a lot runtime info on the screen without using a verbosity control to moderate it. It is straightforward to redirect the output in `run` / `sh` action but not with `R` or `python`. It can be very annoying particularly for some numerical algorithm that dumps large amount of information on the screen at each iteration. It also makes execution extremely slow. Does it sound reasonable that we add a switch to `sos run` to redirect stderr/stdout to /dev/null? ,{},{}
