17700,IssuesEvent,2018-02-11 17:43:58+00:00,120933363,gisaia/ARLAS-server,9483289,elouanKeryell-Even,20204404,gisaia,opened,Collections : add the possibility to specifiy patterns in `index_name`,[],[],0,"In gitlab by @MohamedHamouGisaia on Oct 16, 2017, 11:03

Elasticsearch allow requesting multiple indices using patterns : http://localhost:9200/`index_name*`/_search?pretty

As for now, it is not possible to create collections when we specifiy a pattern in index_name :
```
{
     ""index_name"": ""index_name*"",
     ""type_name"": ""index_mapping"",
      ""id_path"": ""id"",
      ""geometry_path"": ""geometry"",
      ""centroid_path"": ""centroid"",
      ""timestamp_path"": ""startdate"",
      ""include_fields"": ""*""
}
```
A 500 exception is thrown",{},{}
