18055,IssuesEvent,2017-02-22 08:46:03+00:00,2687166,django-crispy-forms/django-crispy-forms,64686,carltongibson,22212844,django-crispy-forms,closed,"Bad alignment of ""Delete"" checkboxes for formsets rendered using table_inline_formset.html",[],[],2,"So I was trying to render a formset as a table with bootstrap 3 and followed the docs, using the table_inline_formset template. 
I wanted the ""Delete"" column name to appear in my table header, and I did not know of any other way besides overriding table_inline_formset.html at line 23:

Original: {% if field.label and not field|is_checkbox and not field.is_hidden %}
Editted: {% if field.label and not field.is_hidden %}

However, this resulted in bad alignment as shown here:
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2179179/4489572/ea8fe120-4a1c-11e4-945d-3eaf86140215.png)

After looking through the elements generated, it seems to be caused by each row's <th> having class ""checkbox"". Changing it to ""form-group"" kind of solved the alignment issues:
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2179179/4489610/82bec4e8-4a1d-11e4-8868-d7a88670d760.png)

Changing line 9 in field.html seemed to solve the problem for me

Original:
<{% if tag %}{{ tag }}{% else %}div{% endif %} id=""div_{{ field.auto_id }}"" {% if not field|is_checkbox %}class=""form-group{% else %}class=""checkbox{% endif %}...
Editted:
<{% if tag %}{{ tag }}{% else %}div{% endif %} id=""div_{{ field.auto_id }}"" class=""form-group...

I'm not sure why checkboxes were treated separately in the first case, maybe there are some cases in which my changes would cause regressions. Or maybe there is a better way to show the delete column?
",{},{}
