18157,IssuesEvent,2016-11-16 15:16:08+00:00,68376693,pybel/pybel,5069736,cthoyt,22892058,pybel,opened,Switch unqualified edge to not use keys,[],"[{'login': 'cthoyt', 'id': 5069736, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5069736?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cthoyt', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/cthoyt', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cthoyt/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cthoyt/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cthoyt/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cthoyt/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cthoyt/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cthoyt/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cthoyt/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cthoyt/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/cthoyt/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"Don't set the key in `pybel.parser.parse_bel.BelParser.add_unqualified_edge` to maintain that all keys for all edges are integers assigned by the default edge key factory in `networkx`, and to make implementing the data models in `sqlalchemy` easier.

This means that there has to be a different way to check that an edge isn't in the graph. My first idea is to check `0 == len(g.edge[u][v])` but that might not be the right thing to do since it could also be possible to have other edges. 

Perhaps iterate over the list of edges in `0 == sum(1 for data for g.edge[u][v].values() if data['relation'] == target_relation)` or some variant of this. Check whether boolean operations, summation, or something else is fastest.

**Alternatively:**

Use `-1` as the key value since it's still an `int()`, it won't violate the rules of the database, and it shouldn't mess up the edge key factory.

Thoughts? @LeKono @cebel @NandithaMallesh ",{},{}
