18278,IssuesEvent,2017-07-12 00:40:09+00:00,88679857,biolink/ontobio,1422171,dougli1sqrd,25489141,biolink,opened,"ontobio.config.get_config() should set default config to Config(), not Session()",[],"[{'login': 'dougli1sqrd', 'id': 1422171, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/1422171?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dougli1sqrd', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/dougli1sqrd', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dougli1sqrd/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dougli1sqrd/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dougli1sqrd/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dougli1sqrd/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dougli1sqrd/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dougli1sqrd/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dougli1sqrd/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dougli1sqrd/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dougli1sqrd/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"Right now, if someone makes `ontobio.golr.GolrSearchQuery` and there is no config file present (default location or otherwise) the ""no config file"" default config code gets run, ultimately in `ontobio.config.get_config()`. This has the code:

    if os.path.isfile(path):
        logging.info(""LOADING FROM: {}"".format(path))
        session.config = load_config(path)
    else:
        session.config = Session()
        logging.info(""using default session: {}, path does not exist: {}"".format(session, path)) 

and we see that in the first line of the `else` block `session.config` is being set to a blank `Session` object. The actual error is present occasionally in tests and in this ticket: https://github.com/biolink/ontobio/issues/64: `AttributeError: 'Session' object has no attribute 'solr_search'`. The `ontobio.config.config.Config` class _does_ have solr_search, so I assume that line is supposed to read: `session.config = Config()`. 

We should instead assign a new `Config()` rather than `Session()`.",{},{}
