18480,IssuesEvent,2017-07-10 02:56:44+00:00,8077625,python-gitlab/python-gitlab,4197151,linuxdaemon,28886265,python-gitlab,opened,JSONDecodeError when getting file contents of a file ending with '.txt' using APIv4,[],[],0," ### Steps to Reproduce
1. Have a file in a gitlab repository with a '.txt' extension
2. Get a v4 Project object from python-gitlab
3. Attempt to retrieve the contents of the file with `project.files.get(""path/to/file.txt"", ref=""master"")`

The `_sanitize` function ( [\_\_init\_\_.py#L48](https://github.com/python-gitlab/python-gitlab/blob/master/gitlab/__init__.py#L48) ) only replaces `/` characters in the file path, but `.` characters must also be sanitized.",{},{}
18491,IssuesEvent,2017-10-12 06:38:12+00:00,36093931,sentinelsat/sentinelsat,1621864,Fernerkundung,29057552,sentinelsat,closed,ReadTheDocs landing page: stable or master? ,"[{'id': 618181481, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/sentinelsat/sentinelsat/labels/discussion', 'name': 'discussion', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'Fernerkundung', 'id': 1621864, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/1621864?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Fernerkundung', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/Fernerkundung', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Fernerkundung/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Fernerkundung/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Fernerkundung/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Fernerkundung/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Fernerkundung/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Fernerkundung/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Fernerkundung/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Fernerkundung/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/Fernerkundung/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",2,"Should the ReadThe Docs landing page default reflect the docs for the latest release or the master branch?

Current default is `stable`, which shows the latest release. Master can still be reached via the dedicated version url: http://sentinelsat.readthedocs.io/en/stable/

I'm asking because our RTD badge points to master. However, I think it should rather point to stable as I expect most users install `sentinelsat` via `pip` not `git clone`.
",{},{}
